dc_title_s: LiDAR-Derived Classified LAS for Marinette County, WI 2014
dc_description_s: This data represents LiDAR-derived classified LAS points for Marinette County, Wisconsin in 2014. Point classification uses semi-automated techniques on the point cloud to assign the feature type associated with each point. LiDAR points can be classified into a number of categories including bare earth or ground, top of canopy, and water. The different classes are defined using numeric integer codes in the LAS files.
uw_supplemental_s: This data is also available as a series of tiles to enable downloads of smaller, more specific areas within the county. To access the tiled data, please visit: https://www.sco.wisc.edu/scoapps/lidar/tile-search/?layer=marinette
